[h3 id=AboutTheGame 
	" About the Game
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	[em 
		"Arrow of Death Part 2
	]em
	" is part 2 of a 2-part text adventure game published in 1983 for home computers. Having successfully completed Arrow of Death Part 1, you now have the components to make a magical arrow with which you will be able to destroy Zerdon, the evil accomplice of the Wizard Akyrz, the real mastermind behind the evil that has befallen the Golden Baton. It is the 4th installment in Brian Howarth's 
	[em 
		"Mysterious Adventures
	]em
	" series.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=AboutTheTas 
	" About the TAS
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"This TAS aims to complete the game as fast as possible.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=Gameplay 
	" Gameplay
	$LF
]h3
[h4 id=TapeLoading 
	" Tape Loading
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"The first ~33% of this TAS is simply loading the tape. Loading finishes on frame 14011 (~4:40).
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=TypingPatterns 
	" Typing Patterns
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"The usual optimal typing pattern looks like this:
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"T
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Y
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"P
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"I
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"N
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"G
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"But a few times, this pattern can be disrupted by typing the 2nd letter of a command 2-3 frames after the first during text loading. Then the pattern looks like this:
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"T
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Y
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"P
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"I
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"N
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"G
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"It's possible to input the 1st letter of a command while a picture is loading. Depending on whether the game lags from this or not, this can save 1 frame every time it's done.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Also, we can only press one key 10 times a second, meaning that when we have to type 2 of the same letter in a row, there's a 5 frame delay.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=WordShortening 
	" Word Shortening
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Words that are 5 letters or longer don't have to be typed out in full, and can instead be shortened to 4 letters, for example:
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" BRAN = BRANCH
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" ZERD = ZERDON
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" TAPESTRY = TAPE
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"You get the idea.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Gameplay continues like this while waiting through cutscenes until input ends on frame 42729, when we enter the command "SHOO ZERD" (SHOOT ZERDON).
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"That's all from me. Thanks for reading.
	$LF
]div
